Text.Value: The UDR-14 LCD screen displays readings and provides indicators of device settings.
The (Dose) Rate Alarm Light flashes (blinks) when RATE ALARM setting is exceeded.
The Dose Alarm Light - flashes (blinks) when DOSE ALARM setting is exceeded.
The RATE button is used to return the device to RATE display and to set the RATE ALARM.
The ALARM button displays the DOSE ALARM and RATE ALARM settings and allows for the adjustment of the settings of these two alarms.
The LIGHT button activates the device's backlight for approximately six seconds.
The DOSE button displays the total accumulated DOSE on the display and is utilized when setting the DOSE ALARM.
The CLR/TEST button is used to move the device into ALARM adjustment mode and to lock in each digit of the new setting.
The ON/OFF button is used to power up and shut down the UDR-14 Radiac Meter.
